			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think pets should be able to see their master. I think that on lower pets, they need "See Invisible" cast on them, but on higher (focus'd) pets it should be innate.
<br />

<br />
Other classes have a LARGE advantage over us, as they are always able to defend in some way. Melee have their weapons and armor already out, priests have armor advantage as well, along with the ability to slow, snare, root or heal themselves. Other int casters have the ability to Mez, Charm, Snare, Root, Fear etc. Mages? We have no armor, we have low hitpoints and what is the magicians biggest (and only) defense? Pet.
<br />

<br />
Would it be ~that~ damn overpowering if we could have our pets with us more often? No other class looses its main source of defense, or its ONLY source of defense while casting a very common and needed spell. 
<br />

<br />
In my mind, it would be very reasonable to request pets have some ability to not die when their masters go into hiding - we are ones with our pets. We communicate with them. We control their life and death with a few simple words. In return, I assume they can sense us, and I don't think a level 60 creature that is commanded by you, connected to you, should suddenly have that connection "sever" because of a level 4 spell. 
<br />

<br />
Anyone else want to see this revised or have any interest in this? I'm curious what the community thinks about this. I don't see any overwhelming factor in this "fix" but maybe I'm being a bit blind because I like the idea <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> Any Input is most welcome. 
<br />

<br />
Kapaal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
