				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi everyone,
<br />

<br />
A 62, non-uber mage here ... 
<br />

<br />
I like the idea of mages as master summoners ... don't forget that we are also supposed to be masters of the elements (given that our epic is the orb of mastery, derived from the elements) ... following that thought, we should be able to:
<br />

<br />
1. manipulate our pet more, without having to wait for AA eg, /pet hold, maybe even suspend pet (perhaps less powerful versions of those abilities without AA)
<br />

<br />
2. Cast different elemental damage spells ie fire based, cold based etc (or at least have them through our pets, which we do, up to a point)
<br />

<br />
3. Summon better focus items (maybe with some +INT, a mix of +HPs, +MANA .... at 62 I don't use any of my summoned focus items except spiked ring)
<br />

<br />
4. Better focus items for pets (after all, we use them up in our epic) ... get a second one?? Duh!!
<br />

<br />
5. Some changes to the way armor and weapons (especially armor) are summoned. In this I would like to see the armor cast OUTSIDE of the bag, and/or the bag which comes with the armor have 100% WR - we can summoned a 100% wr glowing back pack with food and bandages, but with the armor, a non-wr bag??!! come on!
<br />

<br />
Ok, beginning to sound like rant ... I'll stop here <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Deanorn on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
