<br />
Hey Churizo, thanks for your comments. Now for mine ...  not sure how to make the post less messy, but ....
<br />

<br />
For point 1:
<br />
I am not trivialising the hard work put into the AAs ... I'm saying that (I guess partly for the sake of role playing and making the mage "different") since mages are primarily summoners, they abilities should reflect this. Their control over the pet should be better than it is from the start than other classes (maybe this could also be true of say the beastlords class). The "strength" or power of the abilities can be scaled (eg maybe the pets can see invis at some point, and not poof when master goes invis) with only the highest controls obtained through AAs. 
<br />

<br />
For point 2:
<br />
Maybe a major revamp of the mage class is needed ... we get labels of elementalists (which, upon reflection, refers more to our ability to summon elementals, and not dealing with the elements, per se). With this in mind, maybe our spell lines need to be more conjuration- and magic-based, rather than spread out over evocation, conjuration and magic. Perhaps even completely conjuration and magic based spells only, thereby reducing the need to specialise in only one field <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> The conjuration spells could cover the range of elements, or elemental-type summonings .... ice shards, fiery lava stones, (let your imagination run wild a bit here). And yeah, I notice wizzies get that impressive ice comet .... whoo hoo!
<br />

<br />
For point 3:
<br />
Well ... ok ... lol .... one thing that could make mages life intolerable would be the ability to summon a no rent, one charge, no-reagent-needed gate item (maybe to the 7th isle of the plane of air ... LOL). How cool would that be?
<br />

<br />
For point 4:
<br />
Hmmm ... sorry, maybe I missed the point about handling in your focus items (probelm of being a non-epic mage) ... once you get epic, you don't really need the foci for other types of pets do you? ... lol ... but if you did want to use your lower level pets, you'd have to go get the focus item again so that your basic pet could be stronger than normal.
<br />

<br />
For point 5:
<br />
Well ... thank you <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
